Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.38,0:10:56.82,Wing Series Mid-Title,,0,0,0,,{\pos(841.75,367.6)}Mobile Suit Gundam Wing
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.05,0:23:30.07,Wing Next Episode Text,,0,0,0,,{\pos(720.000000,760.500000)}Next Episode
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.07,0:23:58.60,Wing Next Episode Title,,0,0,0,,{\be3\blur3\pos(715.077000,713.250000)}The Fight for Independence
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.43,0:01:30.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.46,0:02:03.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hey! Look at that!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.83,0:02:05.49,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's an Alliance mobile suit!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.58,0:02:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're awake.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.95,0:02:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.25,0:02:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a satellite for\Nmining natural resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.52,0:02:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you doing in\Nthat mobile suit, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.76,0:02:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't appear to be\Na soldier with the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.16,0:02:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.27,0:02:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't try to move, yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.67,0:02:46.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd continued drifting\Nin space, you would've died.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.37,0:02:48.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Why...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.27,0:02:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did you save my life?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.31,0:02:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.84,0:02:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing to do with OZ\Nor the Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.48,0:02:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, this is a neutral zone\Noutside both group's control.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.39,0:03:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.79,0:03:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even say thanks\Nfor saving my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.69,0:03:08.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know where\NI could rent a shuttle?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.49,0:03:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You mustn't!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.49,0:03:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't let a patient in your\Ncondition out of my sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.90,0:03:14.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget about my condition!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.07,0:03:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.77,0:03:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I see you're in a hurry, but\Nit's not good for your health!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.84,0:03:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,What you really need to do\Nis rest your body and mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.71,0:03:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I can make arrangements\Nfor the shuttle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.98,0:03:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Promise you'll wait?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.42,0:03:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.45,0:03:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to ask you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.49,0:03:37.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.09,0:03:39.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But you have to get some rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.93,0:03:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Promise me.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.77,0:03:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.70,0:03:52.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The target is accelerating.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.14,0:03:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The Leos can't keep up\Nwith it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.04,0:03:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The route is unchanged;\Nstill headed for the Bay Area.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.41,0:04:01.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The Leos are no match;\Njust as I thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.11,0:04:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Reports suggest that it\Nmight even be the Tallgeese.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.12,0:04:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care what it is!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.85,0:04:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't allow a mobile suit\Nwith weapons to get too close.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.92,0:04:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,We can probably get rid of it\Nwith the mobile dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.69,0:04:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.03,0:04:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The scientists have completed\Nthe new mobile suits...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.03,0:04:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,...and they're ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.57,0:04:24.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like to test the abilities of\Nthe Vayeate and the Mercurius.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.94,0:04:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't test them in\Nreal battle, you fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.27,0:04:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Who do you recommend\Nfor the other pilot?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.61,0:04:32.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow me to pilot it,\NColonel Une.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.35,0:04:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's got be an excellent pilot\Nto conduct a complete test.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.31,0:04:38.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise he'll get in the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.28,0:04:39.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What's that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.72,0:04:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.85,0:04:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Colonel!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.89,0:04:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa Barton.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.99,0:04:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got command to\Ndestroy the Tallgeese.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.19,0:04:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.17,0:04:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Come out!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.32,0:05:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.12,0:05:14.92,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you like the\NVayeate and Mercurius?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.99,0:05:16.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They're excellent!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.19,0:05:19.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They certainly reflect your\Nskills as Gundam designers.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.09,0:05:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You were right to leave\Nthings in our hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.63,0:05:24.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But this is dangerous!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.56,0:05:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Why are you letting that Gundam\Npilot take out the Mercurius?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.70,0:05:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Because HE IS a Gundam pilot.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.37,0:05:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,OZ should know his piloting\Nskills better than anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.44,0:05:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Can the Mercurius'\Nself-detonation device...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.84,0:05:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...be activated from Trowa's\NVayeate?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.61,0:05:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, just as you requested.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.51,0:05:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Trowa, you have the authority\Nto blow up Mercurius...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.45,0:05:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,...if your pilot acts\Nsuspicious!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.69,0:05:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That shouldn't be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.19,0:05:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,He fought against the\NTallgeese before, in Siberia.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.76,0:05:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,He'd think of this\Nas finishing the battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.29,0:05:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Now the colonies won't be a...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.30,0:06:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...shield to prevent him from{\i0}\N{\i1}finishing it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.70,0:06:03.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How could you have\Nfound out about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.00,0:06:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not hard, seeing as\NI'm a soldier for OZ.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.01,0:06:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a good thing he\Nself-detonated.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.61,0:06:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I was living in the\Ncolony at the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.88,0:06:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So I might not have survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.68,0:06:16.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I should be grateful myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:19.61,Default,,0,0,0,,I found an excellent\Nsubordinate like you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.65,0:06:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How is it?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.12,0:06:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Not too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.39,0:06:56.12,Default,,0,0,0,,The operations are practically\Nidentical to the Gundams'.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.19,0:06:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Not surprising.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.89,0:07:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Hey, Gundam pilot.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.93,0:07:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}How would you fight{\i0}\N{\i1}a mobile doll?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.67,0:07:10.53,Default,,0,0,0,,First I'd sneak behind\Nthe enemy...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,...to make sure I was\Nout of its target range.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.84,0:07:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't overdo it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.28,0:07:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Or I'll have to blow you up.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.58,0:07:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The mobile dolls' weak point...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.45,0:07:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}...is that they have the same{\i0}\N{\i1}abilities as the manned models.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.49,0:07:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}They're identical down to their{\i0}\N{\i1}mobility and reaction times.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.53,0:07:36.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The rest depends on how well{\i0}\N{\i1}a human pilot can fight them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.10,0:07:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Personally, I have a harder{\i0}\N{\i1}time with space mines.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.20,0:07:46.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't need the mobile dolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.10,0:07:48.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll handle that white suit\Non my own.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.98,0:07:52.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We've caught up.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.48,0:07:53.88,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll send the mobile dolls.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.56,0:08:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Why's he in outer space?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.36,0:08:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You got me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.00,0:08:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Mobile dolls!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.35,0:08:33.18,Default,,0,0,0,,My reaction time's a little\Nslower than theirs.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.73,0:08:47.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But I can make up for that\Nin close-range combat...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.67,0:08:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.08,0:09:02.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's two of them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.15,0:09:10.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It reflected the beam!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.10,0:09:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Gotta move in on\Nthis one too!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.01,0:10:03.06,Default,,0,0,0,,They're destroying the\Nmobile dolls...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.14,0:10:05.54,Default,,0,0,0,,...at the same time they're\Nfighting me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.74,0:10:09.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Not many pilots could\Ndo that in outer space.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.85,0:10:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I haven't got time to{\i0}\N{\i1}play games with you.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.99,0:10:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just haul me in.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.20,0:10:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Never would've guessed{\i0}\N{\i1}you'd sneak into OZ.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.83,0:10:29.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Officer Trowa Barton.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.50,0:10:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't believe we've met,\NZechs Merquise.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.61,0:10:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll introduce myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.35,0:10:43.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I go by the name\NMilliardo Peacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.65,0:10:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I've come from Earth\Nas a goodwill ambassador.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.21,0:11:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The majority of people\Nliving in space...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.75,0:11:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,...are either technicians\Nor laborers.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.12,0:11:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Enduring an environment inferior\Nto that of the stable Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.56,0:11:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,...these people have the guts\Nto improve their conditions.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.42,0:11:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This gives rise to a new power.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.19,0:11:15.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the Winner family who\Nsupports this spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.87,0:11:20.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The Winner family master\Nimmigrated...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.57,0:11:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,...and became the central figure\Nin negotiations...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.90,0:11:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,...with the United Earth\NSphere Alliance...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.41,0:11:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...to fight for the rights\Nof the colony residents.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.18,0:11:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Even since the disintegration\Nof the Alliance Military...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.88,0:11:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,...he confronts OZ on\Nbehalf of the colony...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.55,0:11:40.49,Default,,0,0,0,,...but always acts\Nas a pacifist.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.92,0:11:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, Mr. Winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.29,0:11:44.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.46,0:11:47.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre has come back home?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.30,0:11:51.29,Default,,0,0,0,,How old were you in that photo?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.40,0:11:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I really appreciate your\Nbringing me here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.90,0:11:57.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It wasn't any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.47,0:11:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I needed to come anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.25,0:12:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You've been very disobedient.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.52,0:12:10.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I still believe I'm right!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.25,0:12:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply living in outer space\Nis difficult for people!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.26,0:12:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Involving yourself in a war\Nis a waste of time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.43,0:12:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why we've been\Nsearching for solutions...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.63,0:12:25.72,Default,,0,0,0,,...through discussions with the\NUnited Earth Sphere Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.80,0:12:29.86,Default,,0,0,0,,But you had to go to Earth\Nin a mobile suit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.94,0:12:32.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You even gave them an excuse\Nto attack the colonies.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.91,0:12:36.07,Default,,0,0,0,,But someone has to fight\Nor the war won't end.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.18,0:12:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Well?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.28,0:12:38.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Has it ended?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.75,0:12:41.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Did your battle end the war?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.58,0:12:45.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What could you accomplish?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.52,0:12:47.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What could a child like you\Naccomplish?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.92,0:12:49.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The least you could do\Nas an heir...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.96,0:12:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,...is listen to your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.06,0:12:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Use your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.49,0:12:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I think he'll grown up\Nto be an excellent heir.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.26,0:12:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Irea, don't you start on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.67,0:12:59.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.13,0:13:02.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's wrong to think of a child\Nas being incapable.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.47,0:13:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,My little brother will make\Nan excellent heir!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.84,0:13:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Deep inside, Father understands.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.18,0:13:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That dialog with OZ won't\Nlead to any solutions.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.45,0:13:19.15,Default,,0,0,0,,But he thinks things will\Ncome out all right...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.22,0:13:22.15,Default,,0,0,0,,...if the whole colony\Nworks together as one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.59,0:13:25.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell me\Nyou were my sister?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.43,0:13:27.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd heard from Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.19,0:13:29.56,Default,,0,0,0,,...that my little brother\Nwas a Gundam pilot.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.63,0:13:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,But he gets so upset.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.43,0:13:34.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I couldn't decide whether\Nto say anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.17,0:13:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I heard my sisters were\Nstationed...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.44,0:13:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,...in different resource\Nsatellites.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.47,0:13:40.44,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all rooting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.14,0:13:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And Father is no exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.51,0:13:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Right after you left...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.85,0:13:50.51,Default,,0,0,0,,...it was Father who\Nworried about you most.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.58,0:13:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.99,0:13:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true I gave refuge\Nto Instructor H...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.72,0:13:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,...who was fleeing from\Nthe Alliance.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.09,0:14:00.79,Default,,0,0,0,,But from our family's\Nperspective...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.86,0:14:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,...mobile suits aren't needed\Nto attain peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.96,0:14:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, Quatre ignored me and\Ncooperated with the instructor.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.18,0:14:24.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Aggressive solutions only\Nlead to more problems.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.29,0:14:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But Quatre just can't see that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.26,0:14:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,This is where my Gundam\Nwas built.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.96,0:14:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,But I had to destroy it\Non Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.63,0:14:41.57,Default,,0,0,0,,...because of my incompetence.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.20,0:14:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to do?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.97,0:14:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The instructor's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.84,0:14:48.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to make another Gundam,\Nto fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.14,0:14:50.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.18,0:14:54.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you really fight for\Nthe people of the colony?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.45,0:14:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.38,0:15:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Another Gundam pilot who\Nfought like you was caught.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.95,0:15:03.75,Default,,0,0,0,,His Gundam was destroyed\Nto set an example.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.82,0:15:06.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The people of the colonies\Nwere overjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.13,0:15:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,No one in space considers\NGundams their allies anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.20,0:15:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre, are you sure you\Ncan still fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.74,0:15:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I wasn't fighting to be\Nrecognized by the people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.71,0:15:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But one day I believe\Nthey'll see the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.31,0:15:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm probably feeling sentimental\Nwithout Sandrock around.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.35,0:15:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.76,0:15:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm your sister, yet\NI'm always mean to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.26,0:15:38.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Sis...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.49,0:15:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,We all love you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.06,0:15:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't be sad,\Nmy dearest Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.07,0:15:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Irea.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.14,0:15:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Then how would you gentlemen\Ndefine future development?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.71,0:16:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you need arms\Nfor defense?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.18,0:16:02.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.35,0:16:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand your point.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.25,0:16:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're already in a dangerous\Nstrategic position.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.75,0:16:10.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And the people want to be\Nresponsible for their safety.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.56,0:16:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Safety?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.86,0:16:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,This is safety?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.13,0:16:15.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You saw these weapons,\Nand armed yourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.66,0:16:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,How dare you use words\Nlike "safety" or "peace"?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.77,0:16:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Development of this colony\Nwouldn't have been possible...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.74,0:16:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,...without your financial help.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.67,0:16:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,However the current prosperity...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.97,0:16:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,...is a result of the\Ncitizens' efforts.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.01,0:16:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I question your\Ncontinued dictatorship.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.71,0:16:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,When did I act as a dictator?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.01,0:16:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I've merely objected to OZ's\Nintervention...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.15,0:16:37.34,Default,,0,0,0,,...so we could maintain\Ncolony peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.42,0:16:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,If anyone is guilty of trying\Nto dictate the colony...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.59,0:16:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,...it's you men!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.56,0:16:50.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Winner.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.90,0:16:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,At this point, we can't allow\Nyour exclusive control.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.54,0:16:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's decide on a fair offer\Nfor jurisdiction over this area.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.61,0:17:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The manufacture of arms\Nand murder weapons.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.58,0:17:05.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Why should I cooperate?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.85,0:17:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Hand over your rights,\NWinner family!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.72,0:17:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The colony belongs to\Nus laborers!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.55,0:17:14.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooray for OZ!!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.33,0:17:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What are they yelling about?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.30,0:17:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Public opinion is getting\Nstronger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.66,0:17:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Saying we shouldn't\Nmonopolize natural resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.90,0:17:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,That's absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.30,0:17:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true that we own many\Nnatural resource satellites.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.67,0:17:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But we've never monopolized\Nthe resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.11,0:17:35.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We've practically given\Nthem away...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.24,0:17:37.18,Default,,0,0,0,,...for people's prosperity\Nin space.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.24,0:17:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But everybody knew that!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.98,0:17:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,People's feelings have changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.78,0:17:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,About you, and about Father.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.26,0:17:52.59,Default,,0,0,0,,But we're only... we're only\Ndoing the right thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.77,0:18:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The votes are unanimous.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.24,0:18:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,From now on, this natural\Nresource satellite...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.60,0:18:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,...is under OZ's jurisdiction.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.18,0:18:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You won't manufacture weapons\Non this satellite!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.49,0:18:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you serious?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.66,0:18:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Father's disconnected the\Nsatellite?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.76,0:18:29.49,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.56,0:18:31.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, and it's accelerating!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.83,0:18:34.39,Default,,0,0,0,,This could disrupt functions\Nin our entire colony!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.20,0:18:37.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what he's really like!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.24,0:18:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,He's prepared to sacrifice the\Ncolony's future for his benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.11,0:18:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And he won't stop at anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.24,0:18:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Should we allow this to happen?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.72,0:18:52.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Since there are no objections...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.92,0:18:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,...we'll proceed at once to take\Nany necessary steps...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.99,0:18:58.05,Default,,0,0,0,,...to maintain peace in\Nour colony.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.50,0:19:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, you've got to stop this!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.70,0:19:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't going to resolve\Nanything!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.97,0:19:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll be coming after you!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.81,0:19:15.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Are you telling me to sit back{\i0}\N{\i1}as OZ invades the colony?!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.28,0:19:17.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I'm not mistaken!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.31,0:19:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Father!!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.45,0:19:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.38,0:19:22.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Promise you won't fight\Nin those mobile suits anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.82,0:19:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Aggression won't solve\Nanything.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.32,0:19:26.29,Default,,0,0,0,,But Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.83,0:19:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You fools!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.89,0:19:35.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Get away from here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.40,0:19:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That wicked beam cannon\Nis aimed at this satellite!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.07,0:19:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Father, please escape!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.07,0:19:43.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre, I am escaping.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.27,0:19:46.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not putting up a fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.84,0:19:50.17,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no end to this fight,\Nso I've opted to run away.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.88,0:19:53.57,Default,,0,0,0,,If I should die, then so be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.08,0:19:57.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not so attached to space\Nthat I'll compromise myself!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.09,0:19:59.61,Default,,0,0,0,,FATHER!!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.23,0:20:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Father?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.27,0:20:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,FATHER!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.48,0:20:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre!!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.12,0:20:38.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Father...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.49,0:20:40.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.79,0:20:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Father fought very hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.60,0:20:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,He wasn't running away.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.23,0:20:48.22,Default,,0,0,0,,He put up a brave fight, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.57,0:20:52.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Irea, try not to move.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.64,0:20:54.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You'll only make it worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.68,0:20:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You're a kind person, Quatre.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.35,0:21:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And Father was kind too.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.25,0:21:05.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But what did Father do\Nto deserve to be killed?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.32,0:21:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Kind people are shedding tears.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.23,0:21:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But nobody understands them.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.63,0:21:17.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And the colony is satisfied now.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.47,0:21:20.43,Default,,0,0,0,,You people are satisfied!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.97,0:21:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll never forget this.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.01,0:21:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'll make sure the people\Ndon't forget this day, either.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.52,0:22:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Outer space...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.95,0:22:12.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's so quiet...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.86,0:23:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The era plummets into\Nthe depths of confusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.93,0:23:38.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The colonies head down a path\Nleading toward armaments.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.40,0:23:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Zechs has left Earth and\Nconfirms...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.07,0:23:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,...the existence of a Lady Une\Nwho promotes peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.01,0:23:47.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In her goal to achieve\NTreize's ideal...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.87,0:23:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,...Lady Une acts on her own...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:50.01,0:23:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,...against the orders of\Nthe Romefeller Foundation.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.71,0:23:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, on Gundam Wing, Episode 22,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.42,0:23:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Fight for Independence".
